    "response": "As a child of six named Lily found solace in whispering secrets to Mr Buttons – a worn teddy bear with mismatched eyes – who sat poised eternally beside her pillow. She poured out every little joy and fear into his soft blue fur... Early adolescence brought an awareness that stung like betrayal: \"He never whispers back,\ she realized one rainy afternoon after confessing her first heartbreak... By college days spent packing boxes between semesters she would cradle him thoughtfully... \"You taught me how to love something that can't always love you back... Now she understood – parenthood was imminent – that this quiet lesson in tenderness had prepared her for sleepless nights soothing an infant who wouldn't yet smile at her voice... Her fingers traced Mr Buttons’ frayed ear softly as she whispered new secrets now..."
